      "versionNonce": 1443443195,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781069638901,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "-> closure is a combination of function and its lexical environment.\n\n-> When a child function retains access to a value from its parent function even after\n    the parent function has finished executing, this property is called a closure.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "-> closure is a combination of function and its lexical environment.\n\n-> When a child function retains access to a value from its parent function even after\n    the parent function has finished executing, this property is called a closure.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
