      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "const student = {\n    name: \"Sachin\",\n    age:25,\n    city: \"Panipat\"\n}\n\nkey -> name, age, and city (Properties)\n\n-> To access value of key in objects we have to use dot notation and also we can use bracket notation..\n-> When we are using a function in an object at that time that will be known as method.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "const student = {\n    name: \"Sachin\",\n    age:25,\n    city: \"Panipat\"\n}\n\nkey -> name, age, and city (Properties)\n\n-> To access value of key in objects we have to use dot notation and also we can use bracket notation..\n-> When we are using a function in an object at that time that will be known as method.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
